FBIS4-15163 "drsov067_f_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 National Affairs Deputy Blames Energy Industry Crisis on Poor Management Deputy Blames Energy Industry Crisis on Poor Management WS0604090594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 0800 GMT 6 Apr 94 WS0604090594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Ukrainian BFN [Text] Dangerous plans of nuclear industry officials must be put to an end; that was the conclusion made by representatives of public, political, and [word indistinct] organizations gathered at a round table meeting initiated by Green Peace during a press conference for national and foreign journalists. During the conference, the situation and problems of the nuclear power engineering were analyzed. It was noted that its development, according to the old concept of fuel and energy complex management, will not only fail to improve the situation in [words indistinct], but will also deepen economic disproportions and result in unjustified losses of natural resources. Deputy Volodymyr [name indistinct], member of the legislative subcommission for scientific, social, and legal issues related to the Chernobyl catastrophe and nuclear power engineering, pointed out the parochial attitude toward problems of power engineering and narrow-sighted industry management system among factors that aggravated the condition of power engineering sector in 1993-94.
